            <!-- Migration Notes -->
            <note type="migrationNote">Vel 50: Ibn ‘Arabî… wrote it to Abû l-Fawâris Sakhr b. Sinân (owner of the reins of generosity and eloquence) may God grant both of them success. [It is] the transmission of the Sufi … Badr … al-Habashî, freed slave of Abû l-Ghanâ’im Ibn Abî l-Futûh al-Harrânî …</note>
            <!-- Editions, Translations, and Relevant Publications -->
            <noteGrp type="publications">
               <note type="editions">Critical Edition established by Denis Gril and published alongside his French translation Le Livre de l’Arbre et des Quatre Oisaux (Paris, 1984). This text is also reproduced in Angela Jaffray’s English translation The Universal Tree and the Four Birds (Oxford, 2006). Critical edition by ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz al-Manṣūb, based on mss. from the MIAS archive. Published by al-Qudus, Cairo, 2018.</note>
               <note type="translations">English translation by Angela Jaffray: The Universal Tree and the Four Birds, Oxford, 2006 Translated into French by Denis Gril: Le Livre de l’Arbre et des Quatre Oisaux, Paris, 1984</note>
